        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): surface native subagent task updates",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where operators using channel-backed Codex multi-agent runs could not see native subagent lifecycle updates when a Codex native subagent was spawned. The mirrored task rows were hidden from delivery even though the parent run had a real channel target.\n\nFixes #87666.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nNative Codex subagent mirror rows now derive delivery from the parent requester origin. When the parent origin has both `channel` and `to`, the mirrored subagent task is created as `state_changes` / `pending` and retains `requesterOrigin` for direct delivery; when no delivery target is available, orphan/internal mirror rows keep the existing `silent` / `not_applicable` behavior.\n\nThe gateway and embedded Codex runner now pass the resolved delivery context into the harness task runtime scope used by the native subagent monitor. I also checked the sibling Codex source: app-server protocol emits the `thread/started` and `thread/status/changed` notifications consumed here, thread-spawn metadata carries the parent thread id and agent labels, and collab spawn/wait events map into `collabAgentToolCall` items that this mirror already observes.\n\n## User Impact\n\nOperators on channel-backed parent Codex runs can receive native subagent task state changes instead of having mirror tasks hidden by `silent` / `not_applicable`. Internal or orphan native subagent mirrors remain quiet.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-task-mirror.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-monitor.test.ts` (51 tests passed)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/agent-harness-task-runtime.test.ts src/tasks/task-executor-policy.test.ts src/tasks/task-registry.test.ts` (95 tests passed)\n- `npm run tsgo:test:src`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt.CMD --check --threads=1 extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-task-mirror.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-task-mirror.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-monitor.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/native-subagent-monitor.test.ts src/agents/command/types.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/params.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.ts src/gateway/server-methods/agent.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nNot run: live channel proof. This needs a configured channel/gateway environment and maintainer confirmation of the chosen delivery behavior.\n\n`npm run check:changed` was attempted, but it stopped before code checks because `pnpm install` aborted in this non-TTY environment with `ERR_PNPM_ABORTED_REMOVE_MODULES_DIR_NO_TTY`.\r\n",
